main event: Several UFO objects, estimated to be 20-30 in number, were observed by an investigating officer in Duluth, Minnesota on February 26, 1958.
interesting points: The objects were described as football-shaped, with occasional flashing lights, moving at an estimated elevation of 30 degrees and an estimated distance of 5-6 miles.
The objects were observed for 3-5 minutes by the investigating officer.
The objects were reported to interfere with radio signals.
The objects were observed at an altitude of 22,999-33,000 feet at 239 degrees, as reported by visual observation.
The weather conditions at the time of the sighting were documented, including wind direction and velocity.
sighted object: Several football-shaped objects with flashing lights
